'''''Will Gallows and the Snake-Bellied Troll''''' is a 2011 fantasy/western children's book by Northern Irish author Derek Keilty and the first book in the ongoing ''Will Gallows'' series.<ref>{{cite web|title=Year 6 interview with Derek Keilty|url=http://dulwichonview.org.uk/2012/03/16/year-6-interview-with-derek-keilty/|publisher=[[Dulwich OnView]]|accessdate=11 September 2014}}</ref> The book is illustrated by Jonny Duddle, who also illustrated the 2014 Bloomsbury editions of the ''[[Harry Potter]]'' series.<ref name=SL>{{cite news|last1=Harding|first1=Anne|title=Keilty, Derek: Will Gallows and the Snake-Bellied Troll (review)|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-259379661.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103223527/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-259379661.html|dead-url=yes|archive-date=January 3, 2015|accessdate=11 September 2014|publisher=[[School Librarian]] (subscription required)|date=June 22, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=New Harry Potter covers revealed|url=https://www.theguardian.com/childrens-books-site/gallery/2014/jul/30/new-harry-potter-covers-revealed|accessdate=11 September 2014|publisher=The Guardian|date=30 July 2014}}</ref> The book was first published on 3 February 2011 through [[Andersen Press]] and follows the adventures of Will Gallows, a young elfling sky cowboy. It was followed by three entries, ''Will Gallows and the Thunder Dragon’s Roar'' (2012), ''Will Gallows and the Rock Demon’s Blood'' (2013), and ''Will Gallows and the Wolfer’s Deadly Magic'' (2015).

''Will Gallows and the Snake Bellied Troll'' was selected to be part of the  [[Richard & Judy#Richard .26 Judy Book Club|Richard and Judy book club]].<ref name=R&J>{{cite web|title=Will Gallows and the Snake-Bellied Troll (selection and review)|url=https://www.richardandjudy.co.uk/childrens-books/Will-Gallows-and-the-Snake-Bellied-Troll/74|publisher=Richard and Judy|accessdate=11 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=BT>{{cite news|title=I'd love to take the family to Disney, Florida.|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-250834912.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140921211735/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-250834912.html|dead-url=yes|archive-date=September 21, 2014|accessdate=11 September 2014|publisher=Belfast Telegraph (subscription required)|date=February 5, 2011}}</ref>

== Synopsis ==

Will Gallows, a young elfling sky cowboy, rides out on a perilous quest to bring the evil snake-bellied troll bandit, Noose Wormworx, to justice. Noose is wanted for the murder of Will's pa - the former deputy sheriff of Oretown.
Will's journey takes him deep into the heart of the West-Rock, to the dark underground city of Deadrock, where he soon uncovers a deadly secret that could spell disaster not only for Oretown, but for the whole of the West-Rock.

== Reception ==

Critical reception for ''Will Gallows and the Snake Bellied Troll'' has been positive,<ref>{{cite news|title=Will Gallows reitet in die unterirdische Stadt|url=http://www.shz.de/nachrichten/kina/will-gallows-reitet-in-die-unterirdische-stadt-id6030061.html|accessdate=11 September 2014|publisher=SHZ.de/Flensburger Tageblatt|date=18 March 2014}}</ref> and Richard and Judy have praised the book as "A well-written, fast-paced story that’s ‘wild west’ meets fantasy" and had "clever characters".<ref name=R&J /> A reviewer for ''[[The Times]]'' also gave a favourable review for the work, which they deemed "Extremely funny and utterly bonkers”.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Craig|first1=Amanda|title=Will Gallows and the Snake-Bellied Troll by Derek Keilty (review)|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/arts/books/childrensbooks/article2934619.ece |accessdate=11 September 2014|publisher=The Times|date=March 5, 2011}}</ref> ''[[School Librarian]]'' also reviewed ''Will Gallows and the Snake Bellied Troll'' favourably, commenting that the book would appeal to "readers from about eight to twelve, particularly those who like their fiction quirky" and also praised the book for its "ingenious amalgam of western and fantasy with a whole lot of humour added in".<ref name=SL />

=== Awards ===

*''Children's Books Ireland Book of the Year'' (2012, shortlisted)<ref>{{cite news|last1=Newington|first1=Giles|title=Loose Leaves|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-30991914.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327053605/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-30991914.html|dead-url=yes|archive-date=March 27, 2016|accessdate=11 September 2014|publisher=The Irish Times (subscription required)|date=March 24, 2012}}</ref>

== Film adaptation ==

Film rights to ''Will Gallows and the Snake Bellied Troll'' have been optioned by [[Elton John|Elton John's]] [[Rocket Pictures]] and ''[[Shrek 2]]'' director [[Kelly Asbury]] is set to both write and direct the film, which will be a mixture of live-action and [[CGI animation|CGI]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Fleming Jr.|first1=Mike|title=Elton John's Rocket Pictures And Kelly Asbury Follow 'Gnomeo' With 'Will Gallows And The Snake Bellied Troll'|url=http://deadline.com/2011/07/elton-johns-rocket-pictures-and-kelly-asbury-follow-gnomeo-with-will-gallows-and-the-snake-bellied-troll-150260/|publisher=Deadline|accessdate=11 September 2014}}</ref>

